# Stripe Payments

Payment intents are the core primitive for accepting payments in Stripe. A PaymentIntent tracks a payment from creation through confirmation to settlement. You will need a `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` from your [[stripe]] dashboard.

## Create a Payment Intent

```javascript
import Stripe from 'stripe';
const stripe = new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY);

const paymentIntent = await stripe.paymentIntents.create({
  amount: 2000,           // $20.00 in cents
  currency: 'usd',
  payment_method: 'pm_card_visa',
  customer: 'cus_xxx',
  metadata: { orderId: 'order_123' },
});

console.log(paymentIntent.id);            // pi_xxx
console.log(paymentIntent.client_secret); // for client-side confirmation
```

## Confirm a Payment

Server-side confirmation:

```javascript
const confirmed = await stripe.paymentIntents.confirm('pi_xxx', {
  payment_method: 'pm_card_visa',
});
// confirmed.status === 'succeeded'
```

Client-side confirmation uses the `client_secret` with Stripe.js or Stripe Elements — the server creates the intent, the client confirms it.

## Payment Methods

Stripe supports dozens of payment methods beyond cards:

| Method | Type | Use Case |
|--------|------|----------|
| Cards | `card` | Global, most common |
| Bank debits | `us_bank_account` | ACH, lower fees |
| Wallets | `apple_pay`, `google_pay` | Mobile, one-tap |
| SEPA | `sepa_debit` | European bank transfers |
| Link | `link` | Stripe's one-click checkout |

```javascript
// Attach a payment method to a customer
await stripe.paymentMethods.attach('pm_xxx', {
  customer: 'cus_xxx',
});

// Set as default
await stripe.customers.update('cus_xxx', {
  invoice_settings: { default_payment_method: 'pm_xxx' },
});
```

## 3D Secure / SCA

When a payment requires authentication (status `requires_action`), redirect the customer to complete 3D Secure:

```javascript
if (paymentIntent.status === 'requires_action') {
  // Client-side: use stripe.handleCardAction(clientSecret)
  // The customer completes 3DS in a modal or redirect
  // Webhook [[stripe/webhooks]] notifies when complete
}
```

See [[stripe/webhooks#event-types]] for `payment_intent.succeeded` and `payment_intent.payment_failed` events.

## Error Handling

```javascript
try {
  const intent = await stripe.paymentIntents.create({ ... });
} catch (err) {
  if (err.type === 'StripeCardError') {
    // Card declined — err.code: 'card_declined', 'insufficient_funds', etc.
    console.log(err.message);
  } else if (err.type === 'StripeInvalidRequestError') {
    // Invalid parameters
  }
}
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | Server-side API key (`sk_test_...` or `sk_live_...`) |
